  "prompt": "What if I'm depressed with a procrastination habit? How in the world do I get my homework done?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies that might help:\n\n1. Break tasks into very small, manageable steps\n- Start with just 5-10 minutes of work\n- Use the \"2-minute rule\" - if a task takes less than 2 minutes, do it immediately\n\n2. Create a structured environment\n- Set a consistent study space\n- Remove distractions like phone/social media\n- Use apps that block distracting websites\n\n3. Use productivity techniques\n- Pomodoro technique (25 min work, 5 min break)\n- Time blocking\n- Make a detailed to-do list\n\n4. Mental health support\n- Consider talking to a counselor/therapist\n- Explore medication options with a doctor\n- Practice self-compassion\n\n5. Build motivation\n- Reward yourself after completing tasks\n- Visualize the relief of finishing assignments\n- Use accountability partners/study groups\n\n6. Address underlying depression\n- Regular exercise\n- Consistent sleep schedule\n- Proper nutrition\n- Minimize negative self-talk\n\n7. Practical tips\n- Do hardest tasks first when energy is highest\n- Use body doubling (studying near someone working)\n- Set realistic expectations\n\nRemember: Progress is progress, even if it's small. Be kind to yourself in the process.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these strategies?",
